About twenty-six trucks were petrol bombed around South Africa in 48 hours. eNCA reporter, Michael Appel has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - About twenty-six trucks were petrol bombed around South Africa in 48 hours. On Thursday, 20 trucks were torched across four major freeways around Gauteng. READ: Trucking industry 'under siege' Fleetwatch reports that on Saturday night, another six trucks were set alight on the R59 between Sasolburg and the N1. A driver was also shot three times in the leg on the same stretch of road just after midnight. Police say the motive for the attacks is still under investigation. eNCA's Michael Appel shares more details in the video above.